Commentary: wikipedia-mode.el
Description: major mode for editing Wikipedia articles off-line
 A major mode for editing articles written
 in the markup language used by Wikipedia, the free on-line
 encyclopedia <http://www.wikipedia.org>.
 .
 Note: 2012-01-07 the code hasn't been touched since 2006. The
 status in EmacsWiki states that this mode is no longer maintained
 and suggest replacement mediawiki.el
 .
 PATCHES:
 - Support Emacs 23 visual-line-mode
 - wikipedia-mode-hook variable is formally defined.
   Can be set before package is loaded. E.g. you can remove
   `wikipedia-turn-on-longlines' in preference of `truncate-mode'.
